 <p>Ruvane Hammerfrost, Jagorf's Warder(ess)<BR>Officer, Age of Auxilium<BR>Grandmaster Lush<BR>Tanker of Derasinal, Timer of PoGs<BR>I would rather dance on a precipice than behind the safety of castle walls.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E6E6FA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/utalonfar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talonfar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#4B0082>(1/2/02 11:18:46 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://64.38.218.97/stuff/Wrath_Of_God.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ranger needs weapons advice</span><hr size=1> If your looking for max damage output keep &quot;all&quot; the weapons you currently have in both scenarios. Here's why. As a melee character your love of a haste buff is unending, however you don't always have that benefit. Unhasted, try to stay away from that Wurmslayer, its damage to delay ratio is to slow without haste. If you do get into a group with a chanter or shamman bring out the Wurmslayer and watch the damage fly.<br>
<br>
Example:<br>
<br>
With Haste buff, Wurmslayer primary - Centi warhammer secondary<br>
<br>
Without Haste buff, Centi shortsword primary - Centi warhammer secondary<br>
<br>
Your first thought might be that this is alot of equipment to carry around, but you will soon find that there are many different scenarios that you will need to be prepared for. The perfect remedy for this is the Bag of the Tinkerers, but that can be pricy. Try to get both an EE bag (farmable) and a Large Soiled Bag (also farmable).<br>
<br>
In the end &quot;you&quot; need to decide which combinations are best for you considering the situation your in at the time. There are many things a melee charater needs to consider such as speed, damage output, and agro control. All these things can be directly manipulated through the use of different weapons. The more combinations your able to carry on your person at a time the more prepared you will be for any situation. My best advise would be to experiment as much as you can with damage output vs agro. As a ranger a primary concern of yours should be agro management. Sometimes you need to keep a mob on you as primary tank and others you need to keep it off you. Although you have spells that will help accomplish this task your weapons and damage output will always be the deciding factor.<br>
<br>
Also, don't let anyone &quot;tell&quot; you how to play your character... he's your character and &quot;you&quot; should do what you want with him. Find a few combinations that your comfortable with and go from there.<br>
<br>
